 Common social practices such as marriage require the bride to place their hand in the grooms hand, while the groom must place his hand on the brides shoulder in order to indicate to the public whether or not the bride wishes to become married. The public gesture of a yes or no response to marriage is indicated by the groom touching the bride on the back of the neck, and the bride responding by leaning backwards. This is followed by the groom leaning forwards, and the bride leaning backwards. The bride
